  • Classes in zyu19.libs.action.chain.config used by zyu19.libs.action.chain 
    Class and Description
    ChainEditor
    Created by zyu on 2/4/16.
    ChainStyle
    This interface restricts ActionChain to avoid callback hell, and to enable the users of this library to choose a thread for every "action" (or 'PureAction' object).
    Consumer
    This interface's instances are meant to be used as callbacks, in the form of lambda expressions or anonymous classes.
    ErrorHolder
    ActionChain will provide instances of this type through 'Consumer<ErrorHolder>' when an error occurred, to inform the user whether the error may be recoverable.
    PureAction
    This interface's instances are meant to be used as callbacks, in the form of lambda expressions or anonymous classes.
    ThreadPolicy
    This class encapsulates Java.Util's ExecutorService to simplify the process to run an asynchronous call on specified thread.
